🎮 Online Multiplayer Game in Python 🌐
Welcome to the Online Multiplayer Game project! This is a simple implementation of a multiplayer game where two players can connect over a network and move their characters in real-time.

🌟 Features
✨ Key features of this project:

Real-Time Multiplayer : Play with another player on the same machine or over a local network. 🌍
Networking : Uses sockets for communication between players. 🔌
Graphics : Simple visuals powered by pygame. 🖥️
Movement Synchronization : Player movements are synchronized in real-time. ⏳
🛠️ Installation
Follow these steps to set up the game:

Install Python : Ensure you have Python 3.x installed. Download it from here . 🐍
Install Dependencies : Run the following command to install pygame:
bash
Copy
1
pip install pygame
Save the server code as server.py and the client code as app.py. 📂
▶️ Usage
Ready to play? Follow these steps:

Start the Server :
bash
Copy
1
python server.py
Run the Clients :
Open two terminal windows and run:
bash
Copy
1
python app.py
Use arrow keys to move your character.
Watch the other player’s movements in real-time.
🔧 How It Works
⚙️ Quick overview of the game mechanics:

Server : Acts as the central hub to synchronize data between clients. 🌐
Clients : Send their player’s position to the server and receive the other player’s position. 🔁
Game Loop : Updates the screen with both players’ positions in real-time. ⏳
🚀 Extending the Project
Here are some ideas to enhance the project:

Add More Players : Support more than two players. 👥
Add Obstacles : Introduce obstacles or power-ups. 🪨⚡
Custom Themes : Change colors or add animations for a personalized look. 🎨
Sound Effects : Add sound effects for player movements and interactions. 🔊
